{{Infobox musical artist |name = Miki González |image = Miki Gonzalez.jpg |background = solo_singer |birth_name = Juan Manuel González Mascías |image_size = 200px |caption = Miki González in 2006. |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1952|02|14|mf=yes}} |origin = [[Spain]] |genre = ''[[Rock music|Rock]], [[pop rock]], [[Peruvian music]], [[New wave]]'' |instrument = Guitar and vocals |years_active = 1984–present |occupation = Musician, songwriter, singer |associated_acts = [[Mar de Copas]], [[Narcosis (Peruvian band)|Narcosis]], [[Charly García]], [[Andrés Calamaro]]<ref name=" /www.biografias.es" /> |website = }}
'''Juan Manuel González Mascías''' (born February 14, 1952) better known as '''Miki González''', is a Peruvian musician, composer, and producer born in [[Madrid]], [[Spain]].<ref name= mikigonzalez.grupocolca.com>[http://mikigonzalez.grupocolca.com/ Biography of Miki González (in spanish)] Retrieved October 26, 2016</ref> He is recognized as one of the musical icons of the twentieth century, and his songs (such as "Akundún", "Dímelo, Dímelo" and "Vamos a Tocahe) are frequently ranked among the best songs in popular music [[peruvian history]].<ref name= mikigonzalez.grupocolca.com />
Throughout his successful musical career, Miki became famous for being the pioneer in mixing rock with traditional [[Afro-Peruvian music|Afro-Peruvian]] and [[Andean music]].<ref name= www.discogs.com>[https://www.discogs.com/es/artist/1963403-Miki-Gonz%C3%A1lez Miki González in Discogs] Retrieved October 26, 2016</ref>
He has collaborated with many artists, including: [[Mar de Copas]], [[Narcosis (Peruvian band)|Narcosis]], [[Charly García]], [[Cementerio Club]], [[Los Abuelos de la Nada]], [[Andrés Calamaro]], [[Jaime Cuadra]], among others.<ref name=" /www.biografias.es">[http://www.biografias.es/famosos/miki-gonzalez.html Miki González biography] Retrieved October 26, 2016</ref>
He studied and completed his musical training at the prestigious [[Berklee College of Music]] in [[Boston]].<ref>[http://rocanrol.pe/bandas/miki-gonzalez/ Miki Gonzalez] Retrieved June 30, 2017</ref>
