{{Infobox Book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = The Country Blues | image = File:TheCountryBlues.jpg | image_caption = First edition | alt = | author = [[Samuel Charters]] | country = United States | language = English | genre = [[Ethnomusicology]] | publisher = [[Rinehart & Company]] | release_date = 1959 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover|Hardback]] and [[Paperback]]) | pages = 288 (reprint hardcover) }} '''''The Country Blues''''' is a seminal book by [[Samuel Charters]], published in 1959 and generally acknowledged as the first scholarly book-length study of [[country blues]] music.{{fact|date=November 2015}} An [[The Country Blues|album of the same name]] was issued on [[Folkways Records]] as an accompaniment to provide examples of the artists and styles discussed. It was reprinted by [[Da Capo Press]] in 1975 with minor edits, and a new introduction by the author.
